Module IntegrationProject
Package CurrencyConverter

Class IsraeliShekel

java.lang.Object
CurrencyConverter.IsraeliShekel
public class IsraeliShekel
extends java.lang.Object
An object class that utilizes private fields, accessors, mutators, and constructors to store and return the sum of Shekel values as well as display where the Shekel originated.
Author:
Adam Haiken

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors
    Constructor Description
    IsraeliShekel()
    This constructor does not have any arguments and defaults the values of numShekels and originOfCurrency to 0 and "Egypt" respectively.
    IsraeliShekel​(int numShekels, java.lang.String originOfCurrency)
    This constructor contains 2 arguments and allows the developer to pass in two values upon the creation of object "israel" in the driver class.
